# Test-First Development

Write the failing test before writing any implementation. Never write implementation code first.

## Framework

Use Node.js built-in test runner only — no Jest, no Mocha, no Vitest.

```js
// ✅ GOOD
import { test, describe } from 'node:test'
import assert from 'node:assert/strict'

// ❌ BAD
import { expect, describe, it } from '@jest/globals'
```

## Test File Naming

| What's tested | File |
|---|---|
| Existing routes (characterization) | `tests/routes.test.js` |
| Auth middleware | `tests/auth.test.js` |

## Order of Operations

1. Write the test — it must fail
2. Run `npm test` and confirm the failure
3. Write the minimum implementation to make it pass
4. Run `npm test` again — all tests must be green before committing
